setFullpath

public void setFullpath(java.lang.String fullpath)
If the fullpath attribute is set, the file in the fileset is written with the last part of the path in the archive. If the fullpath ends in '/' the file is omitted from the archive. It is an error to have more than one file specified in such a fileset.

パラメータ:
fullpath - the path to use for the file in a fileset.

getFullpath

public java.lang.String getFullpath()
戻り値:
the path to use for a single file fileset.
